          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Acts 9:24",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". On his second visit Saul had remained long enough to nave gathered round him a party of followers who accepted him as their teacher.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and let him down by",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "through",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the wall in a basket",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 11:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " St Paul says, “And through a window in a basket was I let down by the wall and escaped.” Such apertures can be found in the walls of houses in all defenced cities, and it was by such a way that Rahab let the spies escape from Jericho (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 2:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and Michal aided David’s escape (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 19:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The basket here mentioned (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "spuris",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is the same that is spoken of (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 15:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") at the feeding of the four thousand in the mountain district west of the Sea of Galilee. It appears to have been large and soft, fit for carrying a large quantity of miscellaneous articles from the plain into the hills, while the baskets (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cophinoi",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") spoken of at the feeding of the five thousand (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 14:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") were such as the multitude, which in that case had followed Jesus on foot out of the cities, would be likely to carry in their hands. In a basket of the former kind Saul might easily be wrapped and then lowered over the city wall.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 9:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Καθῆκαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "let",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " him ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "down",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") This fact had been known to but few, before that Paul mentioned it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 11:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc., “The God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "knoweth that I lie not.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "” Luke knew most intimately all the affairs of Paul.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
